{
  "_metadata": {
    "file": "foreign-service-pay-tables.json",
    "version": "2026.1",
    "description": "Annual Foreign Service (FS) base pay by grade (FP-1 through FP-9) and step (1-14), 2016-2026. Used for High-3 average salary calculation in FSRDS/FSPS retirement formulas.",
    "effective_date": "2026-01-01",
    "update_frequency": "annual (January, after Executive Order sets FS pay rates)",
    "schema_version": "2.2",
    "sources": [
      "https://www.state.gov/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/2026-FS-Salary-Schedules-for-Web-Publishing-508.xlsx (2026 official schedule)",
      "https://2009-2017.state.gov/documents/organization/266594.pdf (2017 official schedule, anchor year)",
      "https://www.govinfo.gov/content/pkg/GPO-PLUMBOOK-2024/pdf/GPO-PLUMBOOK-2024-10-4.pdf (2024 verification)",
      "OPM January Pay Adjustment Memos (annual base raise percentages)",
      "22 U.S.C. 3963 (Foreign Service Schedule statutory authority)"
    ],
    "_notes": [
      "FS grades are numbered inversely: FP-1 is the most senior, FP-9 is the most junior",
      "Each grade has 14 steps (vs 10 steps for GS). Step progression is time-in-step based",
      "FP-1 steps 10-14 are capped at GS-15 Step 10 base rate",
      "The FS base schedule receives the same across-the-board base increase as the GS schedule",
      "Locality pay for domestic FS employees follows the same locality areas as GS",
      "Overseas Comparability Pay (OCP) replaces locality pay for FS employees posted abroad",
      "Senior Foreign Service (SFS) is a separate open-range pay system linked to SES",
      "All rates are annual base pay in US dollars, before locality/OCP adjustments"
    ]
  },
